(firstQuint)Feasibility of Ambulatory Surgery for Early Breast Cancer.

 The patients with small breast tumours (<2 cm)and clinically node negative disease, were randomized to receive breast conserving surgery and sentinel node biopsy as ambulatory surgery or inpatient-surgery.

Complication rate, patient satisfaction and psychosocial outcomes were compared.

 The psychosocial effects of the treatment mode on their spouses were recorded as well.

